DELTA RIDGE raced off the pace on the outside around the first turn and up the backstretch, began to improve position from the two path coming around the far turn and continued to gain ground mildly in the stretch. THE POINT ROAD hopped up leaving the gate, trailed the field while saving ground through the opening half mile, swung out to the three path for the run around the far turn and never fired. SKY TRAVELER raced in the two path early, continued up the backstretch at the back of the pack, navigated the far bend from the three path and was empty in the lane. STARSHIP MOZART raced in the two path around the first turn, stalked the leader on the outside up the backstretch, dropped back while saving ground around the far turn and tired further in the stretch.

RACE.RACE_TEXT: TAMPA BAY DOWNS RACE 7 1 1/16M Turf CR: 84. Claiming Purse 18600. FOR FOUR YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NEVER WON TWO RACES. Weight, 123 lbs. Non-winners Of A Race At A Mile Or Over Since December 20 Allowed 2 lbs. Claiming Price $25,000 (Races Where Entered For $16,000 Or Less Not Considered In Allowances) (Conditio n Eligibility).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: SMART AS ME raced in the three path around the first turn, settled in the middle of the pack on the outside for the run up the backstretch, began a bid from the four path coming around the far turn, lugged in near the eighth pole, bumping with MOON MISCHIEF in the process and dug in to just get up for the win at the wire. GAMBLING TZAR raced in the middle of the pack between horses through the opening half mile, saved ground around the far bend, began a bid nearing the quarter pole, bumped with MOON MISCHIEF in midstretch and dueled on to the finish, just missing. MOON MISCHIEF raced in the three path early, chased the leaders up the backstretch, challenged from the three path coming around the far turn, was bumped and steadied passing the eighth pole when SMART AS ME drifted into his lane and kept on from there. BLACK SEAL saved ground at the back of the pack through the opening half mile, switched to the three path for the run around the second turn and gained ground late. RONSTADT raced in the three path around the first turn, continued up the backstretch in the middle of the pack on the inside, saved ground around the far bend, improved position in upper stretch and was outkicked late. CARRONADE raced in the two path early, settled off the pace for the run up the backstretch, continued around the far turn still in the two path and showed no kick. CANYOUHEARMENOW raced in the three path around the first turn, led the field on the outside up the backstretch, dueled from the two path around the second bend and tired in the lane. ANVIL raced in the two path through the opening quarter of a mile, pressed the pace on the inside up the backstretch, challenged from the three path coming around the far turn and faded in the stretch. MAGICAL ADVENTURE saved ground around the first bend, trailed the field up the backstretch, raced in the two path around the far turn and was empty from there. A STEWARDS INQUIRY WAS MADE INTO THE STRETCH RUN. UPON REVIEW, HORSE THREE, SMART AS ME, WAS DISQUALIFED AND PLACED THIRD FOR INTERFERENCE NEAR THE EIGHTH POLE.
